content: I added the work log pro to enable exporting the data. For what I use it, I like it.

Best out there but could use a few things.  1. Better export support.  I have to print out my hours and turn it in for each pay period. It really needs to auto fill the file name to reflect the pay period. (Hours_09-05-17_to_09_18_15.csv or Hours_Pay_Period_27.csv, etc..) Right now you have to hit Export > Settings > Spreadsheet File Name > Enter the new file name > OK > Back > Export > Continue ... Otherwise you will overwrite your last export every time.  2. Print and/or PDF support. It's cumbersome to get my hours printed out or sent to my employer in a printable format. Should have option to print from app, or at least support saving in a PDF format for easier distribution.  3. Settings export. I just upgraded my phone. It's awesome that you can export your data and restore it, but it would be nice to have a setting export as well.  4. Better looking widgets. I think the app interface is just fine and don't really care how it looks because it is perfectly functional. The widgets should look a little nicer as they stick out like a sore thumb and don't blend with any theme. At minimum a dark theme option, but rounded corners, color picker for background and text would be great.

If you go to job settings you can "Export all as Spreadsheet" which exports your shifts as a standardized spreadsheet that can be read by any document reader like Microsoft Word, Google Drive and Simple Spreadsheet on Android. replyContent:
Hi, 
Thanks for using Work Log!
When you "Backup Database" Work Log creates a "worklog.db" file in a folder labelled "Work Log" on your local storage, even if you don't complete the export process (a necessity with Android). You can access this file directly from your local storage and do whatever you like with it.

Andrew
